The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing on May 14, 2015 at Camp David. The briefing was led by Press Secretary Josh Earnest and Deputy National Security Advisor Ben Rhodes. They discussed the ongoing summit with the GCC partners, focusing on the topics of Iran, countering violent extremism, the counter ISIL campaign, and regional conflicts in Yemen, Syria, and Libya. They also addressed concerns about Iran’s destabilizing actions in the region, the possibility of an arms race with Iran, and the expectations for a comprehensive deal on Iran’s nuclear program. The leaders discussed strategies to deal with destabilizing actions in the region and the types of capabilities necessary for the security of the GCC partners. They also discussed the possibility of expanding the train-and-equip program for the Syrian opposition and the need for a political solution in Yemen.